commitResults.messageBody: Enable -ea for Gradle run. Add developer assertions in TaskList.add(varargs), Storage.parseLine, and Parser.process to document non-null and format assumptions. These do not replace user-facing validations.

commitResults.messageTitle: A-CodeQuality: refactor Parser with SLAP and constants
commitResults.messageBody:
Refactor Parser.process into small handler methods to follow SLAP
and improve readability. Each handler has a single responsibility,
reducing nested control flow.

Centralize user-facing messages and usage strings as constants to
eliminate magic strings and ensure consistent error handling.

Fix Javadoc, indentation, and line wrapping issues to satisfy
Checkstyle. These changes do not alter behavior but improve clarity
and maintainability in line with CS2103T coding standards.

commitResults.messageTitle: B-Snooze: add 'snooze' command to reschedule deadlines
commitResults.messageBody: Format: 'snooze INDEX /to yyyy-MM-dd'. Only Deadline is supported; Todo/Event produce a friendly error. Persists via Storage.save(); adds Ui.showSnoozed and Deadline.reschedule.
